audio_caption: The audio clip starts with a female speaker's enthusiastic greeting, quickly followed by an apology for being late for school and a brief description of her outfit. Sounds of a café permeate the scene as the speaker announces she will see the listeners on her break. The sounds fade as she says goodbye.  Transitioning to a new segment, the same female speaker expresses relief about being able to talk without stress. She explains that the intro to her vlog was rushed and is now with Oli, who is present but silent. A clatter is heard which she identifies as the delivery of a hummus platter. She mentions they're at Panini Café, across from Pidum, and they've just finished the fall quarter. The speaker asks "Oli" how he feels about the end of the quarter, and he replies "Feels amazing. I'm happy." She acknowledges that it was his hardest quarter.

The audio clip starts with a male voice saying "Done". A female voice then takes over, asking someone to address the viewers, mentioning that people love "Ollie" and want a response. A male voice responds, expressing appreciation for the viewers and mentioning the female speaker informing him about the comments, noting how nice the audience is. The female voice interjects, implying he does not watch the vlogs but only focuses on his appearance in them. The male voice responds, saying he watches them when he has time, adding that he loves the audience. The clip ends with the distinct sound of someone clearing their throat.

The audio begins with a female speaker talking excitedly about the "signature dish" called the "hummus trio" from "Panini Cafe". She notes one is edamame, another is regular hummus, and the last is black bean. She continues in an impressed tone, stating that it's "gorgeous" and mentions the "beautiful presentation".  A male voice then adds a comment about "the spoon placement" also in an impressed tone.  The female speaker responds as if she agrees with the male speaker that "they really thought of everything."

The clip begins with a female speaker discussing "Alistair reading while he was reading my presentation" and showing "Festi, but like my other presentation," clarifying it's the one she did for class. She mentions it's slightly different because "our teachers asked for different stuff," and emphasizes her desire to make the app. She concludes by asking for comments about downloading it. The speaker is enthusiastic and conversational. Concluding her statement, she requests the listener's feedback for whether they would download the app. Light background music plays, providing a cheerful, pop-like atmosphere. A male voice in the background interjects with "That's cool".

The clip begins with a female speaker excitedly presenting her "caprese sandwich" and describing it as her "new thing", mentioning it may be from a French place and expressing her love for it. She then notes a bow tie pasta salad. A male speaker joins in, mentioning his "nice turkey melt" along with a "chicken". The female speaker agrees that the food is "beautiful". Following this food discussion, a male voice is heard discussing the idea of a "happy ending". Overlapping this, a female voice humorously remarks about someone wanting to go home in a suitcase, followed by unintelligible speech. All this occurs over a background of ambient noise.

The clip starts with sounds of an environment, followed by a female speaker beginning a vlog update, apologizing for the lack of recent content due to a hectic day preparing for a flight. She explains that she's at LAX with a friend, Megan, who greets the audience, with the speaker mentioning they missed their "Squirtle". She notes, with dismay, having cracked the screen on her camera that day.

The clip begins with someone saying "We missed our flight". The speaker then says that she would say it's "half our fault and half not our fault". She states that she's going to "take some responsibility for this", mentioning being on American Airlines. In the background, there is indistinct speech and general airport-like noise, indicating the setting.

Two young women are recording a vlog. They have had a frustrating experience at an airport and are speaking in an informal, conversational tone about a missed flight due to issues with checking in their dog. One woman recalls a confrontation with an airline representative.  Following their story, upbeat pop music with a slight alternative edge begins to play in the background, and the women sing and laugh along, seemingly mimicking how they feel when listening to 21 Pilots. One asks for embarrassing screenshots to be found and shared on social media. Their tone transitions to a more reflective one as they describe how tired they look, and discuss how "this is really just a new level of look." A brief moment of silence transitions back to the initial storytelling tone where one of them finishes the story about missing the flight, expressing frustration with the airline's lack of assistance.

The audio clip starts with a female speaker sharing travel details, mentioning a morning flight and a layover in Phoenix. She expresses annoyance, due to the inconvenience it causes for the pet Squirrtle. Her tone is conversational and slightly exasperated. She then mentions the length of their travel day, calling the vlog a "total flop" because it was the "busiest day of my life." There is background noise present, and then she spots a car parked on a building, but then guesses it is a light. She asks if she should end her vlog and will try to film airport and travel footage and concludes the vlog. A second female voice then calls out "thumbs up for my routine," and the first female voice says "thumbs up for Megan, and Squirrtle, and vlogmass." The clip ends with a reflective tone. The clip also included ambient sounds.

The audio begins with a female speaker saying "Okay, I'll see you guys tomorrow" in a casual tone. This is followed by music in an electronic genre with a chill and somewhat melancholic mood. The music appears to feature synthesizers and heavy processing, giving it a lo-fi and atmospheric quality.
